CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 23, 1959, page A15, reads: "Key To The City - The key to the city was presented to Mrs. Cora pg. Maloney (second from left), councilwoman of Buffalo, N.Y. who was speaker for the Business and Professional Women's Founders Day breakfast at the Hotel Penn - Sheraton Sunday morning. Mrs. Irma D'Ascenzio, extreme right, Pittsburgh councilwoman, made the presentation. Others, left to right, are Mrs. Gladys Howell, program chairman; Mrs. Maloney and Councilman Paul F. Jones."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, including, from left to right, Gladys Howell, Cora P. Maloney receiving the key to the city, Paul F. Jones, and Irma D'Ascenzio, gathered at the Hotel Penn Sheraton, another version
